DESCRIPTION
Compare original vs replayed artifacts, randomize order to reduce position bias, optionally support swapped-order judging, and produce win/tie/loss outcomes with reasons.

DESIGN
## Plan (attempt 2)

**Approach:** Add a library-only PairwiseEvaluator mirroring RubricEvaluator discipline (head-validate EvalRequest, guard nil Judge, build a method-tagged JudgeRequest, call Judge, map JudgeResponse -> eval.Evaluation with Score{Kind:ScorePairwise}). Canonical orientation is PINNED: req.Targets[0]=original=A, req.Targets[1]=replay=B. Position bias is mitigated by randomizing the ORDER targets are PRESENTED to the Judge, then back-mapping the position-relative winner to canonical A/B. CRITICAL FIX (attempt 1 blocker): the swap decision is derived PER-PAIR by mixing the evaluator Seed with a stable per-pair identity, so presentation order varies across a cohort yet stays reproducible. Adds opt-in DoubleJudge mode (bead text: 'optionally support swapped-order judging'). Also fills the validateJudgeOutput 'pairwise' arm.

